Why path required?

Path Environment variable, which is used to locate packages, there are used to 
convert source code to machine-readable binany format.

How the Operating System will identify the corresponding executable file?

Operating System will search the Environment variable path, it has locations
contains executable files.

with help of Path we can,
    To execute commands properly, 
    Convert source code to machine readable binany format.



